The paper proposes an unsupervised graph neural network for heterogeneous graph representation learning, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also utilizes information theoretic-based learning algorithm, which is a common technique in the field of natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, the likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
